@startuml
title C2 - Diagrama de Contenedores - AngeloDjangoOrders

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  BorderColor #334155
}

actor "Usuario\nCliente/Admin" as User

rectangle "Navegador Web" as Browser {
  rectangle "HTML + CSS + JS\nBootstrap local" as Frontend
}

rectangle "Docker Compose\nangelow" as Compose {
  rectangle "Contenedor web\nPython 3.14 + Django 5.2.8" as Web {
    rectangle "Proyecto dcrm" as Dcrm
    rectangle "App website" as Website
    rectangle "Templates y static local" as Static
  }

  database "Contenedor db\nMySQL 8.4" as DB
}

rectangle "docker/entrypoint.sh" as Entrypoint
rectangle ".env / variables de entorno" as Env

User --> Browser : usa la interfaz
Browser --> Web : HTTP :8000
Frontend --> Static : carga estilos y scripts
Web --> DB : ORM Django / MySQL\nhost db:3306
Env --> Web : credenciales DB
Env --> DB : credenciales MySQL
Entrypoint --> Web : migrate + runserver
Compose --> Web : build Dockerfile
Compose --> DB : volumen angelow_mysql_data

note right of Web
C2 muestra las partes grandes:
navegador, aplicacion Django,
base de datos MySQL y Docker.
end note

@enduml
